<main class="main-faq">
    <div id="FAQ">
        <p class="title">FAQ'S</p>
        <p class="title">Application Related Questions</p>
        <div class="accordian application-faq">

            <div class="item">
                <div class="FAQ-title">
                    <p class="faqQuestion">1. What kind of water quality analysis do you offer?</p>
                    <span class="expandToggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="FAQ-content">
                    <p>We offer comprehensive water quality analysis for both drinking and irrigation purposes. Our system evaluates the water quality based on parameters such as pH, turbidity, hardness, dissolved oxygen, BOD, COD, and more. Additionally, we assess irrigation suitability using factors like Sodium Adsorption Ratio (SAR) and Sodium Percentage (Na%).</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="item">
                <div class="FAQ-title">
                    <p class="faqQuestion">2. Who can use your water quality reports?</p>
                    <span class="expandToggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="FAQ-content">
                    <p>Our water quality reports are designed for both individual users and government agencies. Individuals can use the reports to assess the quality of water for personal use, such as drinking or irrigation, while government agencies can utilize the data for public health assessments and policy-making.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="item">
                <div class="FAQ-title">
                    <p class="faqQuestion">3. How is the water quality data presented?</p>
                    <span class="expandToggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="FAQ-content">
                    <p>The water quality data is presented in detailed reports featuring graphs, tables, and location-specific information. The data includes key water parameters such as pH, TDS, turbidity, and more, making it easy for users to understand the water quality in a specific location.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="item">
                <div class="FAQ-title">
                    <p class="faqQuestion">4. Can I view water quality data for specific locations?</p>
                    <span class="expandToggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="FAQ-content">
                    <p>Yes, our reports include detailed geographical data such as latitude and longitude. You can view water quality assessments for specific locations, making it easier to assess the suitability of water for drinking or irrigation in different areas.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="item">
                <div class="FAQ-title">
                    <p class="faqQuestion">5. What are the main parameters you analyze for irrigation water?</p>
                    <span class="expandToggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="FAQ-content">
                    <p>For irrigation water, we analyze the Sodium Adsorption Ratio (SAR) and Sodium Percentage (Na%), which are key indicators of water suitability for agricultural purposes. Our reports also include other relevant data such as TDS and pH to help farmers and agricultural professionals make informed decisions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            
            <div class="FAQ-ShowMore">
